As a future user of OS/2 (I've grown weary of Windows...see a previous 
posting), I have a basic question that bothers me just a little. 

Why does everything seem to revolve around Windows? I do understand that
Windows does dominate the market (or at least it seems to) and therefore
from an economical standpoint software-makers are best served by writing
programs for Windows. But if OS/2 is a superior product, why are there not
numerous programs made for OS/2? From my viewpoint (and its limited), it
seems that most popular titles are "for Windows," which seems to mean that
OS/2 must emulate Windows to run them. Why is there not industry support
(software) to make titles "for OS/2"? 

Just a curious new user. Thanks!!

			M.L. (a.k.a. Satchmo)


