The best OS/2 strategy that I've seen so far has been that of CA, who  
offer both their Windows & OS/2 packages in 1 box.  That way, they don't  
lose either way, & neither do their sales suffer (unless of course the  
product is bad to start with.)  I dunno how good they are in their  
respective markets, or how much better their windows s/w is compared to  
their OS/2 s/w, but I am impressed by the way they are going; their  
commitment to the platform seems far stronger than Lotus'.
